text: Kédougou is a region in the southeast of Senegal. The regional capital is Kédougou. It was created in 2008. As of the 2013 census, 152,134 people lived there. It has an area of . == Départements == There are three départements: * Kédougou Département * Salémata Département * Saraya Département Category:2008 establishments in Africa Category:Regions of Senegal
